.TH "task_work_run" 9 "task_work_run" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
task_work_run \- execute the works added by task_work_add()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" task_work_run
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Flush the pending works. Should be used by the core kernel code.
Called before the task returns to the user-mode or stops, or when
it exits. In the latter case \fBtask_work_add\fP can no longer add the
new work after \fBtask_work_run\fP returns.
